            "answer_text": "For \u201cfor: Elizabeth\u201d, you may write \u201c(Name of receiver) \u6536\u201d (meaning \u201creceiver receives\u201d). For \u201cfrom: Anne\u201d, just write \u201c(your name) \u8d08\u201d (which means \u201cyou sent\u201d) on the card. Since we don't usually write the names of either the sender or receiver on gifts, why not instead consider attaching a card inside the present with your message written. That would be more heartwarming. ",
